        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 2:36PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 236 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Texas Creek, or 52 miles southwest of Colorado Springs, moving
northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cotopaxi and Texas Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
